body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting Car Solutions. My name is Emily Clark. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hello, my name is Alexis Jones.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Alexis. How can I assist you today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I have been having some issues with data management related to my recent car purchase.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I understand the importance of smooth data management. Can you provide me with your phone number and email address for verification purposes?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure. My phone number is nine eight seven six five four three two one zero and my email is alexis.jones@email.com.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for sharing that information, Alexis. Is there any other personal information you can provide to help us assist you better?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: My home address is five six seven Park Avenue, Cityville.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Alexis. We will look into your data management issue and get back to you shortly. Thank you for your time.

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Thank you for your help. I'm feeling relieved now. Goodbye.
